<article id="forms">
  <h2 class="pos-heading-2">Forms</h2>
  <p>There are two ways for styling form controlls. You can add a <code>pos-form</code> class to a container and make all the child inputs styled automatically or you can add one of the following classes to any single input to style it separately.</p>

  <h3 class="pos-heading-4 styleguide-heading-4">Basic example</h3>
  <form action="" class="pos-form pos-form-simple styleguide-example">
    <fieldset>
      <label for="styleguide-form-example-a">Email</label>
      <input type="email" id="styleguide-form-example-a" placeholder="Email address" required>
    </fieldset>
    <fieldset>
      <label for="styleguide-form-example-b">Password</label>
      <input type="password" id="styleguide-form-example-b" placeholder="••••••••" required>
    </fieldset>
    <fieldset>
      <label for="styleguide-form-example-c">Message</label>
      <textarea id="styleguide-form-example-c" placeholder="Your message"></textarea>
    </fieldset>
    <fieldset>
      <input type="checkbox" id="styleguide-form-example-d" required>
      <label for="styleguide-form-example-d">An agreement</label>
    </fieldset>
  </form>
